92
00:04:06,497 --> 00:04:08,206
I know he gets her.

93
00:04:08,241 --> 00:04:09,916
Is this how she died?

94
00:04:09,951 --> 00:04:11,384
Definitely.

95
00:04:14,653 --> 00:04:18,156
STEVE: So, Tom, why'd you
bring me up into this room?

96
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:21,226
I saw a solid-black mass
moving down the wall.

97
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,793
I was stunned.

98
00:04:22,828 --> 00:04:25,496
TOM: After that, it was
almost like a siege mentality,

99
00:04:25,497 --> 00:04:27,716
where you kind of hunker down
at night

100
00:04:27,751 --> 00:04:29,936
and just hope
that nothing would happen

101
00:04:29,971 --> 00:04:31,770
and wish for the daylight
to come.

102
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:36,041
At night, I've heard
heavy objects moving.

103
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:37,843
I come here
and look at the desk,

104
00:04:37,878 --> 00:04:39,310
and nothing had moved.

105
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:42,649
It's something that I'm not
equipped to deal with.

106
00:04:44,917 --> 00:04:48,621
AMY:
There's a guy down there.

107
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:52,723
He's saying,

108
00:04:52,758 --> 00:04:55,759
"Don't come down here.
Get away from me."

109
00:04:55,794 --> 00:04:58,965
Often, it's not easy
for the dead to understand

110
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,433
that I'm there to help.

111
00:05:02,735 --> 00:05:05,503
This is wrong.

112
00:05:05,538 --> 00:05:10,576
There's a lot of problems here,
specifically in this area.

113
00:05:10,611 --> 00:05:13,310
And it became obvious
in that moment

114
00:05:13,345 --> 00:05:16,548
that the angry man
was agitated by my presence.

115
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,818
Can you talk about
what he does up here

116
00:05:18,853 --> 00:05:20,385
that might
disturb people?

117
00:05:20,386 --> 00:05:23,889
I'm hearing, like,
stuff sliding across the floor.

118
00:05:23,924 --> 00:05:25,257
Like,
hearing furniture moving.

119
00:05:25,292 --> 00:05:28,261
He will really go nuts.

120
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:34,433
STEVE: Tom's daughter, Allyson,
had several encounters

121
00:05:34,434 --> 00:05:36,969
that would have been damaging
to any kid.

122
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:39,570
First,
I was afraid of the dark,

123
00:05:39,571 --> 00:05:43,142
but then
I was afraid of the ghost.

124
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:44,277
A ghost.

125
00:05:44,312 --> 00:05:45,377
Like a man?

126
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:46,410
Yes.

127
00:05:46,445 --> 00:05:49,748
He just stands
by the front of my bed.

128
00:05:51,416 --> 00:05:53,618
But it was Tom's wife
who really concerned me

129
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:55,821
because the thing
that was haunting her the most

130
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,357
were here memories.

131
00:06:02,461 --> 00:06:04,563
Joanna, where are you
actually from?

132
00:06:04,598 --> 00:06:05,698
I'm from Poland.

133
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,331
Okay.

134
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:09,902
My father worked
with the government,

135
00:06:09,937 --> 00:06:12,238
and he was involved
with police.

136
00:06:12,273 --> 00:06:15,041
That's my father.

137
00:06:17,242 --> 00:06:19,910
What did he do
for the government?

138
00:06:19,945 --> 00:06:22,813
He would be the part
of spying on people,

139
00:06:22,848 --> 00:06:26,819
or trying to get rid of
everybody who was in his way.

140
00:06:26,854 --> 00:06:30,621
But my mom was opposite side
of the politics.

141
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:35,494
And my father, I think he had
anger issue or something,

142
00:06:35,529 --> 00:06:39,363
because I saw him holding gun
against her head.

143
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:44,803
JOANNA:
That was first time I was not
feeling safe around my father.

144
00:06:44,838 --> 00:06:49,206
And it's kind of difficult
talking about him,

145
00:06:49,241 --> 00:06:53,595
but Steve was very
understanding, very supportive,

146
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:57,950
and somebody who'd help us
to bring things to normal.

147
00:06:57,985 --> 00:06:59,485
Do you talk to them
at all?

148
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,951
They divorced
when I was 18,

149
00:07:00,986 --> 00:07:04,123
